Definition.WordDefinition: Id \Id\, n. (Zo["o]l.) A small fresh-water cyprinoid fish ({Leuciscus idus} or {Idus idus}) of Europe. A domesticated variety, colored like the goldfish, is called {orfe} in Germany. [1913 Webster]

Definition.WordDefinition: id \id\ ([i^]d), n. (Psychoanalysis) That part of a person's psyche which is the unconscious source of impulses seeking gratification or pleasure; the impulses are usually modified by the {ego} and {superego} before being acted upon. [PJC]
